Starting next Monday, National Vegetarian Week will be focusing on the environmental benefits of giving up meat. Where better to celebrate than at London’s most glamorous vegan restaurant – Saf in Shoreditch. Whether you’re a raw food junkie or a hardcore herbivore, you’ll love their vegan-friendly approach to fine dining. Throughout Veg Week, Saf are offering a special Power Lunch deal that starts with a deliciously guilt-free salad of herbs, radishes, sprouts, flowers and citrus miso dressing. To follow, there's a choice of spicy coconut laksa with tofu and mushrooms; whole grain pasta puttanesca; or Saf’s botanical burger – a high protein vegan burger on a wholemeal bun with lettuce, micro sprouts, tomatoes and mushroom sauce. Priced at just £8.25, the team can even serve the two courses together to get you recharged and back to work within the hour. Also, on Monday, the restaurant is hosting its first wine club dinner with a ‘celebrate Spring’ theme. The dinner will be held in their private dining room from 7pm and guests are invited to bring along a bottle of ‘Spring’ wine – whatever that might mean. As Saf is passionate about organic and biodynamic wine, the bottle you bring should be naturally produced and vegan-friendly. Rather than a small flight of tasty canapés, Chef David Bailey has created an impressive seven-course botanical menu full of fresh flavours and seasonal produce. Dishes will include steamed spring asparagus with leek vinaigrette; mushroom and white truffle risotto; and South American tacos filled with pineapple salsa, tomato chutney and homemade guacamole. If you’ve still got room, there’s lychee granite and chocolate orange torte for dessert. Guided by sommelier Joe McCanta, you will get a chance to discuss the wines on offer, the various regions they come from, the processes used, and – most importantly – how well they match the food. Tickets are priced at £50 per head and you can secure your place by emailing Joe at joe.mccanta@safrestaurant.co.uk. Looking for vegetarian food elsewhere? Check out our 'Best For Vegetarian' list.
