On May 5th, Mexico will be commemorating their victory over the French Empire at the Battle of Puebla in 1862 with traditional Cinco de Mayo festivities. If you fancy getting in on the action without leaving the capital, why not celebrate in style at some of London’s most popular Mexican restaurants? At Wahaca in Covent Garden, they’re celebrating by launching a new summer menu focusing on fresh flavours and lighter options – perfect for warm weather dining. On May 4th and 5th, they’re celebrating by giving away a shot of Gran Centenario’s Blanco Tequila to every customer. Don’t miss out! It’s all change at Benito’s Hat in Goodge Street where they’re unveiling a new bar and introducing some new tequila cocktails with summery flavours like watermelon and apple. On Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday next week, they’re running a two-for-one deal on the new drinks so grab a friend and join the queue. If you’re lucky enough to live or work near Leather Lane, you probably already know about Daddy Donkey. If you don’t, head down for lunch mid-week and grab a burrito to go. They’re among the best you’ll find in London, and their tacos are pretty good too. Look out for the lime green van on nearby Whitecross Street too – Luardo’s does pretty much the same thing with similar success. For burritos on the run, you can’t go wrong with Chilango. The Fleet Street original and new Upper Street branch are both excellent and won’t do much damage to your wallet. Want to eat Mexican elsewhere? Try Tortilla in Islington or Southwark; Santo or El Camino on Portobello Road; Nineteen Ten at Westfield; or Mercado in Stoke Newington. Arriba!
