Diners at the Rossopomodo pizzerias can look forward to being refused cutlery and encourage to get stuck in, Neapolitan style. The chain - which has branches in Covent Garden, Chelsea and Notting Hill - was originally founded in Naples and is passionate about staying true to its Italian roots. Even the water they use to make their coffee comes from Naples. \"We make traditional Neapolitan pizza, and anyone from Naples will tell you, you don't eat pizza with a knife and fork. It's crazy using cutlery,\" said Rossopomodoro's managing director Simone Falco. \"Pizza is something you touch and share. The pleasure of eating it is just as much about how it feels as how it tastes.\" Simone and his team are enforcing the no cutlery rule, and will confiscate any knives and forks brought in by customers so fall in line and get hands on. Bring the kids - they'll love it!
