New research from leading burger restaurant chain, GBK, has revealed that the vast majority of students starting university this Autumn can't cook simple meals from scratch. They surveyed 300 18-21 year olds across the UK and discovered that 66% couldn't cook an omelette, while one in six couldn't put together a traditional roast. While 88% could manage to prepare beans on toast, only 23% could make fresh soup and many relied heavily on pre-prepared food. David Sykes, Managing Director at GBK, explained: \"While I expected a lot of young people were used to having their food cooked for them, I was surprised by how few were able to cook pretty basic meals.\" \"To make sure students are getting proper, wholesome food into them, we're offering a special 'you buy one, we'll buy one' deal on all of our burgers when they produce our exclusive student voucher. I'd challenge even the hungriest of students to polish off two of our filling burgers, even if one of them is free, so bring a mate!\" The offer is valid for students only, Sunday - Thursday, when you eat at any Gourmet Burger Kitchen in the UK. Just buy two burgers and the cheapest one will be free. Offer runs until 31st October 2008 and you can print your voucher from the GBK site or the STA Travel site.
