Chilango, which means a person living in Mexico City, is a new Mexican restaurant arriving in London with a mission to deliver fast, fresh and tasty Mexican food to the masses. Owners Eric Partaker and Dan Houghton have spent two years researching the best burrito and taco to come up with the most popular formula (taking into account traditional Mexican versions as well as US versions in California etc). They explain: ‘Our name sums us up. We’re here to bring some vibrant Latin spirit to the streets of London.” Set to launch this October on Fleet Street, the interior will be a mix of bold, modern colours and the menu will feature typical Mexican fast food with a twist. Everything will be prepared and cooked fresh daily in the open kitchen, with chicken marinated overnight in their secret marinade and the guacamole mashed by hand. Most importantly, it’s all on offer at bargain prices – which should go down well as we all tighten our belts and the media talk us into a recession. If you can’t wait for Chilango’s doors to open, you could try the equally cheap new addition to Goodge Street – Benito’s Hat. The menu is small – just soups, salads, burrito and tacos – but they do these very well indeed. They have already had a rave review in the Metro and our users have reported ‘great tasting beef, salsa verde and guac’ and, predictably, long queues. Not so new but still worth visiting are Mucho Mas on Upper Street, which serves up ‘simply delicious burritos’ and ‘organic juices’ and nearby Tortilla – famous for its authentic street food. KL explains, ‘Tortilla a tiny, fast-food-esque place directly across from Angel, and specializes in the simple, inexpensive Mexican food that I came to know and love back in the States...I had the lush grilled steak burrito with everything, doused with Cholula hot sauce at the table. I may have to swing by for the braised pork on my way home.’ If you’re lucky enough to live or work near Leather Lane, you probably already know about Daddy Donkey. If you don’t, head down for lunch mid-week and grab a burrito to go. They’re among the best you’ll find in London, and their tacos are pretty good too.
