This Autumn, award-winning chef Theo Randall has teamed up with Pizza Express and created four new pizzas for the season’s menu. Having worked at the River Cafe before opening his own restaurant at the Intercontinental Hotel in Mayfair, Theo is famous for his passion for quality ingredients. The new pizzas use the original Pizza Express dough recipe, but add new ingredients like fresh uncooked mozzarella, Fontal cheese from Trentino, and the same brown shrimps he uses in his own restaurant. The shrimps are accompanied by grated zucchini, creme fraiche, grand padano, lemon and chilli on Theo’s Gamberettini pizza. For veggies, there’s the Piemontese – yellow and red peppers with garlic, red onions and nutty Fontal cheese – and tuna fans can feast on the Tonnara – yellowfin tuna, olives, anchovies, garlic and capers. We popped into the Farringdon branch yesterday and tried out Theo’s Favorita. The crisp oval base arrived topped with with hand-torn fior di latte mozzarella, translucent layers of parma ham, nicoise olives and plenty of rocket. The cheese isn’t melted so it feels a lot lighter than the usual Pizza Express offerings, and with all the rocket you could almost pretend it’s healthy. Served on platters with pizza cutters and priced between £8.25 and £10.95, they’re probably more expensive than your usual order but we reckon they’re worth every penny.
