***TITLE
La Tasca Opens At Old Spitalfields
***AUTHOR
city-eating
***DATE
2008-10-01 12:09:00
***CONTENT
Following a multi-million pound refurbishment, Old Spitalfields Market looks...almost finished, with shiny new restaurants filling the spaces in the illuminated glass cubes that overlook the market. Horner Square – so new even GoogleMaps can’t find it – is already home to a Gourmet Burger Kitchen, Las Iguanas, Canteen and other fast and friendly eateries guaranteed to keep the local City boys well fed all year round. Self-proclaimed ‘mega-brasserie’, Le Bouchon Breton, opens this week and John Torode’s new venture, The Luxe, is set to follow in 2009. The newest addition, though, is a branch of Spanish super-chain La Tasca. We popped in last night to check it out and – as you’d expect – it’s full of Spanish flags, bright colours and paintings of bulls and matadors, but it looks rather good. We had barely sat down to browse the menus before a smiling waitress brought over glasses of fruity sangria. It was delicious, and that’s coming from someone who doesn’t usually touch the stuff – even in Madrid. With hungry journos and gangs of PR people spilling through the doors, the staff were like a well-oiled machine, ferrying bread baskets and bitesize morsels of Spanish omelette from table to table. Normally at this sort of thing you have to wrestle the canape wench to the floor and prise any freebies out of her fingers, but not so at La Tasca. We watched, open-mouthed and ravenous, as enormous pans of paella were carried aloft to the front of the restaurant and generous portions were spooned on to waiting plates. There were different types – one with chicken and chorizo, one with mussels and plump prawns – and they were all delicious; hot, fragrant and eagerly washed down with the jugs of sangria that arrived at each table. It’s a rarity to see a smile on a waiter’s face these days, so the full-on grins at La Tasca were a nice surprise. If standards stay this high, we’ll be back to try out the tapas. It certainly beats queueing in the rain for Barrafina!
